She is best known for her work on Saturday Night Live, The Daily Show and The Office.[1] In 2016, she co-created the TBS comedy series Angie Tribeca with her husband, Steve Carell.
data.text:
Nancy Ellen Carell (née Walls; born July 19, 1966) is an American actress, comedian and writer. She is best known for her work on Saturday Night Live, The Daily Show and The Office.[1] In 2016, she co-created the TBS comedy series Angie Tribeca with her husband, Steve Carell.

In 1995, she married Steve Carell.[2]
